44 SECTION 2.2. G.S. 14-415.11 reads as rewritten:
45 "§ 14-415.11. Permit to carry concealed handgun; scope of permit.
46 (a) Any person who has a concealed handgun permit to carry a concealed handgun may
47 carry a concealed handgun unless otherwise specifically prohibited by law. The person shall carry
48 the permit together with valid identification whenever the person is carrying a concealed
49 handgun, shall disclose to any law enforcement officer that the person holds a valid permit and
50 is carrying a concealed handgun when approached or addressed by the officer, and shall display
51 both the permit and the proper identification upon the request of a law enforcement officer. In
Page 2 House Bill 674-First Edition

