1 that the defendant is prohibited from possessing, purchasing, or receiving or
2 attempting to possess, purchase, or receive a firearm for so long as the
3 protective order or any successive protective order is in effect. The terms of
4 the order shall include instructions as to how the defendant may request
5 retrieval of any firearms, ammunition, and permits surrendered to the sheriff
6 when the protective order is no longer in effect. The terms shall also include
7 notice of the penalty for violation of G.S. 14-269.8.
8 (2) The sheriff may charge the defendant a reasonable fee for the storage of any
9 firearms and ammunition taken pursuant to a protective order. The fees are
10 payable to the sheriff. The sheriff shall transmit the proceeds of these fees to
11 the county finance officer. The fees shall be used by the sheriff to pay the costs
12 of administering this section and for other law enforcement purposes. The
13 county shall expend the restricted funds for these purposes only. The sheriff
14 shall not release firearms, ammunition, or permits without a court order
15 granting the release. The defendant must remit all fees owed prior to the
16 authorized return of any firearms, ammunition, or permits. The sheriff shall
17 not incur any civil or criminal liability for alleged damage or deterioration due
18 to storage or transportation of any firearms or ammunition held pursuant to
19 this section.
20 (d1) Transfer to Licensed Firearms Dealer. – After the defendant surrenders possession of
21 all firearms, machine guns, ammunition, and permits to the sheriff pursuant to subsection (d) of
22 this section, the defendant may enter into an agreement with a qualified licensed firearms dealer
23 to take possession of the surrendered items from the custody of the sheriff if (i) the defendant is
24 the owner of the items and (ii) the items have been in the custody of the sheriff at least 15 days.
25 The defendant shall authorize the qualified licensed firearms dealer to submit the form provided
26 for in this subsection requesting the transfer of the firearms, machine guns, and ammunition to
27 the sheriff currently storing the items. The qualified licensed firearms dealer must present the
28 completed form and a copy of the dealer's valid federal firearms license to the sheriff, who shall
29 have 24 hours to facilitate the transfer of the firearms, machine guns, and ammunition to the
30 dealer. Any funds received from the sale of a firearm, machine gun, or ammunition by a
31 defendant pursuant to this subsection are the property of the defendant. The defendant's permits
32 to purchase firearms and permits to carry concealed firearms shall remain in the care and custody
33 of the sheriff as provided in subsection (d) of this section.
34 At the time a qualified licensed firearms dealer takes possession of the firearms, machine
35 guns, and ammunition, the dealer shall provide a copy of the record required to be maintained
36 under federal law upon the receipt or disposition of the firearm, machine gun, or ammunition to
37 both the sheriff and the owner of the firearms, machine guns, and ammunition.
38 A qualified licensed firearms dealer that accepts firearms, machine guns, and ammunition
39 pursuant to this subsection shall not (i) release the firearms, machine guns, or ammunition to the
40 defendant unless the motion for a protective order is dismissed or any order of surrender has
41 expired or (ii) transfer possession of the firearms, machine guns, or ammunition to any person
42 the dealer knows or reasonably should know will allow the defendant to exercise care, custody,
43 possession, ownership, or control of the firearms, machine guns, or ammunition, and any
44 violation of this prohibition is a Class 2 misdemeanor.
45 The Administrative Office of the Courts shall create a form for use in transferring firearms,
46 machine guns, and ammunition from the custody of the sheriff to a qualified licensed firearms
47 dealer pursuant to this subsection. The form shall require the notarized signatures of both the
48 defendant and the qualified licensed firearms dealer and shall allow for either the storage or sale
49 of the firearms, machine guns, and ammunition by the qualified licensed firearms dealer. The
50 form shall also include information concerning the defendant's rights to recover the surrendered
51 firearms, machine guns, or ammunition.
